{"kind":"article","metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"AppcuesKit"}],"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article","title":"Configuring the Appcues URL Scheme"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"abstract":[{"text":"The Appcues iOS SDK includes support for a custom URL scheme that supports previewing Appcues experiences in-app prior to publishing and launching the Appcues debugger.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/appcueskit\/urlschemeconfiguring"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Configuring the Appcues URL scheme involves adding a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CFBundleURLTypes"},{"text":" value and then directing the incoming URL to the Appcues iOS SDK.","type":"text"}]},{"style":"note","name":"Note","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"It is ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"strongly"}]},{"type":"text","text":" recommended that you configure the custom URL scheme. It allows non-developer users of your Appcues instance to test Appcues experiences in a real setting. It’s also valuable for future troubleshooting and support from Appcues via the debugger."}]}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Register the Custom URL Scheme","anchor":"Register-the-Custom-URL-Scheme"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Update your "},{"code":"Info.plist","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to register the custom URL scheme. Replace "},{"code":"APPCUES_APPLICATION_ID","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" in the snippet below with your app’s Appcues Application ID. This value can be obtained from your "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/studio.appcues.com\/settings\/installation","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For example, if your Appcues Application ID is ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"123-xyz"},{"text":" your url scheme value would be ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"appcues-123-xyz"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":null,"code":["<key>CFBundleURLTypes<\/key>","<array>","    <dict>","        <key>CFBundleTypeRole<\/key>","        <string>Editor<\/string>","        <key>CFBundleURLName<\/key>","        <string>$(PRODUCT_BUNDLE_IDENTIFIER)<\/string>","        <key>CFBundleURLSchemes<\/key>","        <array>","            <string>appcues-APPCUES_APPLICATION_ID<\/string>","        <\/array>","    <\/dict>","<\/array>"],"type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Handle-the-Custom-URL-Scheme","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Handle the Custom URL Scheme"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Custom URL’s should be handled with a call to "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Appcues\/filterAndHandle(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Appcues\/didHandleURL(_:)","isActive":true},{"text":". If the URL being opened is an Appcues URL, the URL will be handled.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If your app uses a Scene delegate, add the following:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["func scene(_ scene: UIScene, willConnectTo session: UISceneSession, options connectionOptions: UIScene.ConnectionOptions) {","    \/\/ Handle Appcues deep links.","    let unhandledURLContexts = appcues.filterAndHandle(connectionOptions.urlContexts)","","    \/\/ Handle any links remaining in unhandledURLContexts.","}","","func scene(_ scene: UIScene, openURLContexts URLContexts: Set<UIOpenURLContext>) {","    \/\/ Handle Appcues deep links.","    let unhandledURLContexts = appcues.filterAndHandle(URLContexts)","","    \/\/ Handle any links remaining in unhandledURLContexts.","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If your app uses only an App delegate, add the following:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["func application(_ application: UIApplication, open url: URL, options: [UIApplication.OpenURLOptionsKey : Any] = [:] ) -> Bool {","    \/\/ Handle Appcues deep links.","    guard !appcues.didHandleURL(url) else { return true }","","    \/\/ Handle a non-Appcues URL.","    return false","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A SwiftUI app can handle the custom URL scheme as part of the "},{"code":"onOpenURL","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" modifier associated with the "},{"code":"Scene","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" of your main ","type":"text"},{"code":"App","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["var body: some Scene {","    WindowGroup {","        MyApp()","        .onOpenURL { url in","            guard !appcues.didHandleURL(url) else { return }","        }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Verifying-the-Custom-URL-Scheme","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Verifying the Custom URL Scheme"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Appcues debugger allows you to easily validate that the Appcues deep link is properly configured."}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Launch the debugger in your app with a call to ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Appcues\/debug()","type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Expand the debugger by tapping the floating button."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Tap the “Appcues Deep Link Configured” row to verify the status. If a checkmark appears, the Appcues deep link is properly configured."}]}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"level":3,"text":"Troubleshooting","type":"heading","anchor":"Troubleshooting"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Error 0"},{"type":"text","text":": The Appcues debugger was unable to set up the verification test."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"Error 1","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CFBundleURLSchemes"},{"type":"text","text":" value is missing. Refer to the “Register the Custom URL Scheme” section above."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Error 2"},{"text":": The URL scheme is registered, but the Appcues SDK did not receive the link from the host app. Refer to the “Handle the Custom URL Scheme” section above.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Error 3"},{"type":"text","text":": The Appcues SDK received the link, but the verification token value was unexpected. Testing again should resolve the issue."}]}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Debugging","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" for details on the functionality of the debugger.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/GettingStarted","doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Identifying","doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Tracking","doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/AnchoredTooltips","doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/PushNotifications","doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Appcues"],"title":"Core Functionality"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/com.appcues